XWizard is a simple service for monitor configuration running on top of systemd and xrandr.

It is packaged for debian systems using the improper buildeb way [1].

[INSTALLATION]
# To build the deb package type:
$> ./xwizard.buildeb
$> sudo dpkg -i XWizard.deb
$> systemctl --user start xwizard.service
# Each interested user might enable the service at the start-up:
$> systemctl --user enable xwizard.service


[1] https://ans.disi.unitn.it/users/baldesi//ubuntu/bash/deb/2017/02/10/hello-deb.html
